      • lockTimeSkipping

        public void lockTimeSkipping(java.lang.String caller)
        Disables time skipping. To enable back call unlockTimeSkipping(String). These calls are counted, so calling unlock does not guarantee that time is going to be skipped immediately as another lock can be holding it.

      • unlockTimeSkipping

        public void unlockTimeSkipping(java.lang.String caller)

      • sleep

        public void sleep(java.time.Duration duration)
        Blocks calling thread until internal clock doesn't pass the current + duration time. Might not block at all due to time skipping.
